  "prompt": "If I buy wireless Bluetooth headphones with a USB charger, will they work like wired headphones if they're plugged into my computer usb via USB cable?",
  "response": "No, wireless Bluetooth headphones with a USB charger typically cannot function as wired headphones when plugged into a computer via USB cable. Here's why:\n\n1. **USB for Charging Only**: The USB port on most Bluetooth headphones is designed solely for charging the internal battery. It does not transmit audio data.\n\n2. **Audio Transmission via Bluetooth**: Audio is transmitted wirelessly via Bluetooth. Even when connected via USB, the headphones rely on Bluetooth for audio communication with the device.\n\n3. **No Analog Audio Support**: Unlike wired headphones that use a 3.5mm audio jack or other analog audio connection, Bluetooth headphones do not have the hardware to process audio signals through the USB port.\n\nIf you want to use your headphones in wired mode, check if they come with a 3.5mm audio jack or support a wired connection via an auxiliary cable. If they do, you can use them with your computer or other devices that have a headphone jack. Otherwise, you'll need to rely on Bluetooth for audio transmission.",
